Certainly, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "strast" in different forms and positions, with translations in English:

1. *Strast* je ono što čini život vrednim življenja. (*Passion* is what makes life worth living.)
2. Ona je *strast*vena plesačica. (She is a *passionate* dancer.)
3. Njihov odnos je pun *strasti*. (Their relationship is full of *passion*.)
4. *Strast*veni poljubac ih je spojio. (A *passionate* kiss brought them together.)
5. Oni su *strast*veni kolekcionari knjiga. (They are *passionate* book collectors.)
6. *Strasti* su se smirile nakon svađe. (*Passions* have calmed down after the fight.)
7. Njegova *strast* za sportom ga je dovela do Olimpijade. (His *passion* for sports led him to the Olympics.)
8. *Strast*veno volim ovu pesmu. (I *passionately* love this song.)
9. *Strasti* su bile visoke na sastanku. (*Passions* were high at the meeting.)
10. Ona živi svoju *strast* kao umetnica. (She lives her *passion* as an artist.)

Note: In the Serbian language, nouns and adjectives are declined to reflect their grammatical roles in a sentence, which means that the form of the word "strast" changes depending on its function in the sentence. In the sentences above, the word "strast" appears in various forms, including "strasti," "strastvena," and "strastveno."